<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="store-n">store <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /stɔː(r)/    美 /stɔːr/  </p>
<p>[C]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>商店：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>keep a department store 
经营一家百货店</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>贮存；储存品：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>have a store of food
贮藏食物</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>仓库：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Rainforests are often called the world’s drug store.
热带雨林常被称作世界的药品库。</p><footer>2009 安徽</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="in-store">in store</h3>
<p>1.<strong>贮藏着；准备着；即将发生：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Squirrels have enough nuts <strong>in store for</strong> their winter hibernation.
松鼠为冬眠准备了充足的坚果。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She wondered what fate had <strong>in store for</strong> her next.
她想知道等待她的会是什么样的命运。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Check carrots, potatoes, onions and any other vegetables <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ store and immediately use or throw away any which show signs of rotting.  （2014 湖北改）  </li>
<li>When she first arrived in China, she wondered what the future might have <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ store for her, but now all her worries are gone.  （2008 湖北改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. in   2. in   </p></div>